headline.main: Frank Lloyd Wright Dies; Famed Architect Was 89; Leader in Modern U. S. Style of Building -- Stirred Controversy Frank Lloyd Wright, Leader of Modern Architecture School, Dies in Phoenix at 89 ICONOCLAST NOTED FOR STRONG IDEAS Believed Form in Building Should Follow Function -- Once Foe of Skyscrapers

snippet: PHOENIX, Ariz., April 9 -- Frank Lloyd Wright, regarded by many as the greatest architect of the twentieth century, died early today in St. Joseph's Hospital. He was 89 years old.

byline.original: Special to The New York Times
